    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "it just feels so heavy though. like if the logic is that everything is temporary and ultimately meaningless, then the most logical and peaceful thing to do would be to just stop fighting. if there's no grand purpose, then why is there this intense pressure to just keep enduring the pain and the struggle? wouldn't it actually be more rational to just embrace the nothingness instead of struggling against it?",
